        <updateDate>2008-01-04T15:26:53Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Climate Neutral Electricity Generation Act of 2007 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a tax credit for investment in a climate neutral combustion facility. Defines &quot;climate neutral combustion facility&quot; as any facility which: (1) burns matter to produce electricity; (2) captures and uses carbon dioxide released during combustion to recover hydrocarbon fuel; and (3) produces no emissions of mercury or greenhouse gasses and no emissions that form fine particulate, smog, or acid rain</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
